<TITLE> 4.5% VAT on coaching centres, English medium schools </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnews24.com)  Finance adviser Mirza Azizul Thursday proposed to slap a 4.5 percent VAT on coaching centres, English medium schools, private medical and engineering colleges and private universities. "I also propose to impose VAT on the basis of truncated base value of the coaching centres, English medium schools, private medical and engineering colleges and private universities at the rate of 4.5 percent," he said in his budget speech. He also proposed to extend the same truncated base value facility to photo lab, courier service and air-conditioned bus services. "In order to widen the VAT net, I propose to bring immigration advisers within this net." "At the same time I propose to withdraw existing VAT exemption facility from ornamental fish, specialised doctors, lawyers and dental clinics." bd
